The number of individuals receiving
help for over-indebtedness from the Portuguese Association for
Consumer Protection rose 25 percent in the ten months through
October from the same period a year earlier.  A total of 4,525 people are being assisted by the consumer
protection group, up from 3,628 in the previous year,  DECO  said
today in an e-mailed report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
